task.summary: Default task
Fixed imports on each file.
Added new components and modified some inheritance with the components.
Added functionality to execute script components.
Implemented the basis for dynamic layer rendering.
Refactored component names.
Integrated the render system's scene creation before the main game loop starts
Had entities be removed from the render scene automatically when they were destroyed from the world.
Added a dynamic layer mechanism in the RenderSystem. This is to simulate a z-coordinate/depth in the 2d scene.
Added a name variable to script components for easy identification
Scripts are special types of components. They do not derive from the component base class. This might be changed later.
Made the render/physics system access the important components of an entity through variables instead of using get_component(). Did some variable name refactoring
Removed the inheritance of Component->Script
Bug fix. Each entity will now have each of their scripts take input.
Added variables to entity class for quick access to important components
In the physics system, replaced the collision_event() with an event queue
In the physics system, replaced the collision_event() with an event queue
Updated the special entity types (ex. GameObject)
refactored create box collider object
Updated the engine. Updated the driver to test the new modifications.
Made the move function in the physics system be called before collision resolution.
Updated the physics
Added circle collider objects to test
Added the circle collider object class as a special type of entity
Added a function to create circle collider entities
Added circle to circle and circle to box collision response
Added walls around the screen edge for collision testing
Fixed the circle to circle collision. The circle to box collision is not ready yet.
Fixed the circle to circle collision. The circle to box collision is not ready yet.
Made the circles be affected by gravity in the test driver.
Fixed circle to box collision detection. Still need to work on better collision response in general, such as sliding between colliders.
